BEGIN DESCRIPTION:
g01 is organically created from XS_Cutline_input.csv, showing how RAS RAS fills the 16-char XS CutLine field with as many digits as fit (~15 significant figures), stripping trailing zeros. RAS truncates rather than rounds. The input 1675270.36345064855 was saved as ...36345064 where rounding would give ...065. 

g02 and g03 are shifted with  blocks/xs_gis.py, with RS 3000 shifted 100 ft, RS 2000 shifted 105 ft, RS 1000 shifted 10 ft. g02 shifts to the right and g03 shifts to the left.
